	"keywords": "Gatsby, Gatsbyjs, RSS Feed, Blog, Canonical URL, SEO",
	"description": "With the recent exodus from Medium [https://medium.com] many developers are now\ncreating their own GatsbyJS Blogs and then cross-posting to Medium\n[https://medium.com] or publications like freecodecamp.org [/news/] and dev.to\n[https://dev.to].\n\nCross-posting is time consuming, but necessary to drive traffic to your personal\nsite. Let&#x27;s look at how we can automate this by adding an RSS feed to your\npersonal GatsbyJS blog.\n\nAdd Canonical URL&#x27;s to Your Blog\nWhat is a canonical url?\n\nA canonical url",
